thyme honey: 

    Thyme honey is a versatile ingredient that can enhance a variety of dishes. It pairs particularly well with roasted meats, poultry, and vegetables, as well as cheeses and baked goods. Its unique flavor profile also makes it a great addition to dressings, marinades, and even desserts. 


    Roasted Chicken:
    Thyme honey adds a delicious sweetness and subtle herbal note to roasted chicken thighs or a whole chicken.

    Glazed Ham:
    Thyme honey can be used to create a flavorful glaze for ham, offering a sweet and savory combination. 

    Drizzle thyme honey over roasted carrots, sweet potatoes, or Brussels sprouts for a delicious and visually appealing side dish. 

    Grilled Cheese:
    A grilled cheese sandwich with thyme honey and fig jam is a delightful combination of sweet, savory, and tangy flavors. 

    Baked Feta:
    The sweetness of thyme honey complements the salty and tangy flavor of baked feta cheese. 
    
    Halloumi:
    A drizzle of thyme honey enhances the flavor of pan-fried halloumi, especially when paired with red pepper flakes. 

    Compound Butter:
    Thyme honey can be combined with softened butter, salt, and fresh thyme to create a flavorful spread for toast, grilled corn, or vegetables. 
    
    Thyme honey can be incorporated into marinades for meats or used to create a unique salad dressing. 
    
    Thyme honey can be added to frosting for cakes and cupcakes, providing a subtle herbal sweetness. 
    
    Thyme honey can be used to create a flavorful syrup for drizzling over mini cakes or other baked goods. 
    
    Thyme honey can be incorporated into ice cream or used as a topping, adding a unique flavor dimension. 
    
    Mix thyme honey into Greek yogurt for a simple and delicious snack or dessert. 

